.TH HSH 1 "December 2023" "1.0" "HSH Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh \- simple shell command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a basic UNIX command line interpreter. It reads commands from standard input and executes them.

.SH USAGE
The shell can be used in interactive mode by running ./hsh. It displays a prompt "$ " and waits for user input.
Commands are executed by typing them and pressing enter.

.SH FEATURES
.IP \[bu]
Executes commands from the PATH
.IP \[bu]
Handles command lines with arguments
.IP \[bu]
Implements built-in commands: exit, env
.IP \[bu]
Handles the PATH environment variable
.IP \[bu]
Implements error handling

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell
.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic command:
.B $ ls
.TP
Command with arguments:
.B $ ls -l
.TP
Using PATH:
.B $ pwd
.TP
Full path command:
.B $ /bin/ls

.SH EXIT VALUES
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 127
Command not found

